## 5. Risks and Solutions

**Purpose:**  
To think ahead about possible problems during the project and define solutions that help reduce risk and keep the project realistic and achievable.

| Risk Area | What could go wrong? | How to reduce the risk (solution) |
|---|---|---|
| **Technology** | Technical difficulties with telemetry integration, anomaly detection logic, machine learning tuning, or communication between components. | Start with simple rule-based logic, keep ML lightweight, test components separately, and build progressively. |
| **Timeline** | Aircraft or hardware integration may take longer than expected. | Use replayed CSV scenarios in parallel and review progress regularly. |
| **Team** | With only two team members, workload may become unbalanced. | Keep the MVP focused, define responsibilities clearly, and communicate regularly. |
| **Testing** | The system may not behave the same way with real data as with replayed scenarios. | Validate with multiple scenarios and progressively move from replayed data to real telemetry. |
| **Deployment** | Integration between Guardian, database, dashboard, and aircraft telemetry may be difficult. | Fix the telemetry and alert schemas early, test modules independently, and integrate step by step. |
| **Scope** | The project may become too broad. | Keep the MVP limited to telemetry anomaly detection, structured alerts, and human-in-the-loop decision support. |

